Adam tried to write $x^4 + 5x^2+4$ as a product of linear factors. This is his work:

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=} x^4 + 5x^2+4
\\\\
&= \blueE{(x^2+4)}\maroonE{(x^2+1)} &&\gray{\text{Step 1}}
\\\\
&= \blueE{(x^2+4)}\maroonE{(x+i)(x-i)} &&\gray{\text{Step 2}}
\\\\
&= \blueE{(x+i\sqrt{2})(x-i\sqrt{2})}\maroonE{(x+i)(x-i)} &&\gray{\text{Step 3}}
\end{align}$

**In what step did Adam make his first mistake?**

[[☃ radio 1]]

